images.text_verbatim:
Weldment Drawing
STEEL NOTES
1) ALL DIMENSIONS ARE IN INCHES UNLESS NOTED OTHERWISE.
2) WHERE NO WELD SYMBOL IS SHOWN, ASSUME FILLET ALL AROUND, WITH SIZE EQUAL TO THE LESSER OF 1/4" OR THE MINIMUM THICKNESS OF ADJOINING FACES, UNLESS NOTED.
3) STRUCTURAL STEEL PLATES, ANGLES, AND CHANNELS SHALL CONFORM TO CSA G40.21-300W, G40.21-350W CLASS C FOR HSS AND W SECTIONS.
4) WELDING SHALL CONFORM TO THE REQUIREMENTS OF CSA STANDARDS W59 AND SHALL BE UNDERTAKEN BY A FABRICATOR AND ERECTOR FULLY APPROVED BY THE CANADIAN WELDING BUREAU TO THE REQUIREMENTS OF CSA STANDARDS W47, DIVISION 1 OR DIVISION 2.1.
5) FIELD VERIFY ALL DIMENSIONS PRIOR TO MANUFACTURING.
6) ALL STRUCTURAL STEEL TO BE FINISHED AS APPROVED BY THE CONTRACTOR/OWNER.
7) ALL HARDWARE TO BE TORQUED BY TURNOFNUT METHOD AS PER S1619 23.7.2, AND TABLE 7.

DESIGN LOADS
1) DESIGN LOADS ARE UNFACTORED UNLESS NOTED OTHERWISE:
A) DEAD LOADS: SELF-WEIGHT OF STEEL
B) LIVE LOAD (MAX.CAPACITY): AS PER LOAD TABLE ON THE FIRST PAGE OF THIS DRAWING PACKAGE
images.summary: This section contains detailed steel notes and design load specifications for the weldment drawing. Key points include: all dimensions are in inches unless noted otherwise; fillet welds are assumed where no symbol is shown, with size equal to the lesser of 1/4" or the minimum thickness of adjoining faces. Structural steel must conform to CSA G40.21 standards, and welding must meet CSA W59 standards, performed by approved fabricators. Field verification of dimensions is required before manufacturing. All hardware must be torqued by the Turnofnut method. Design loads include dead loads (self-weight of steel) and live loads as per the load table. These notes ensure compliance with CSA standards and proper fabrication practices.
